Czech Stocks: CEZ, Komercni Banka, NWR Shares Move in Prague

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-09-21T15:12:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/czech-stocks-cez-komercni-banka-nwr-shares-move-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s PX equity
index rose 2.4 percent to 929 by its 4:28 p.m. close in Prague.
The benchmark fell 6.2 percent in the previous three days to the
lowest since July 2009.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CEZ AS (CEZ)  , the biggest power utility in the country,
jumped the most since May 2010, rising 3.6 percent to 725
koruna. The government will distribute about a third of carbon-
dioxide emission permits to domestic energy companies free of
charge until 2020,  Lidove Noviny  reported today, citing
unidentified people close to the  Finance Ministry .  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB)   advanced 3.2 percent to 3,120
koruna, adding to a 0.8 percent gain yesterday. The Czech unit
of Societe Generale SA said in a regulatory filing yesterday it
had repurchased 65,900 of its own shares since Aug. 23.  New World Resources Plc (NWR CP) slid 0.7 percent to 147.4
koruna, its lowest close since August 2009. The biggest Czech
producer of coking coal had its price estimate cut to 234 koruna
from 308 koruna at J&T Banka, which cited reduced forecasts for
coal prices. J&T kept NWR on “buy” in a report today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
